properties.name: <![CDATA[Finchale Priory (English Heritage)]]>
properties.cmt: <![CDATA[St Godric founded this Priory - he was a merchant and pirate, turned hermit. He spent the last 60 years here as a hermit, praying in the River Wear, and rescuing stags. He also composed songs, dreaming the music into being with the help of the Virgin Mary. His hymns are the earliest known recorded songs with music and words side-by-side.]]>

properties.name: <![CDATA[HM Prison Frankland]]>
properties.cmt: <![CDATA[Some of the most dangerous prison inmates in the country are kept here in Class A security. It is a dark place to walk past but certainly gives you pause for some kind of reflection. But don't let it get you too down!]]>

properties.name: <![CDATA[St Oswald's Church, Durham]]>
properties.cmt: <![CDATA[King Oswald defeated the ruler Cadwallon ap Cadfan at Heavenfield, and he helped St Aidan found Lindisfarne, who then taught Cuthbert, who ended up making Durham famous.]]>

properties.name: <![CDATA[Mount Joy]]>
properties.cmt: <![CDATA[The moment you first see Durham Cathedral is from this hilltop view. In medieval times, this place was so named because it provides joy but also sometimes tears of joy, and some pilgrims would fall to their knees weeping. Arguably as soon as you see the Cathedral you have arrived in one sense.]]>
